tracks.title: Morning Cup Of Joe
tracks.desc: A sweeping banjo and a wheedling slide guitar to start the day with and etch a daylong smile to the lips.

tracks.title: Lighthouse Lament
tracks.desc: The banjo gallops through this breezy ballad, warbled by the lap steel with weathered electric backing.

tracks.title: Clever Little Gent
tracks.desc: A gawky vaudeville waltz led by the piano and an unwavering sense of grace in response to its stylistic antiquity.

tracks.title: Daveno Orchestra
tracks.desc: Nothing like the tango on a shag carpet, with a shout out to the crowded, delightfully dysfunctional orchestra, who go out with an explosive finish, all playing in unison.

tracks.title: New Ford Model T
tracks.desc: Like digging through the costume drawer and finding grandpa's old suits, this genre hopping, vocal-based old timer is worth hours of fun.

tracks.title: Too Many Donuts
tracks.desc: A dopey, sluggish waltz, with gluttonous brass and a rhythm begging to zonk out.

tracks.title: Reawakening
tracks.desc: Subtle percussion and bass weave a mellow rhythm for a romantic guitar, synths add a warm vibe as a song fleshes out with an upbeat and loving melody.

tracks.title: Regular Like Seasons
tracks.desc: Bass and guitar weave an elegant and subtle melody. The warm but serious notes and languid pace speak of introspection and deep thoughts. Ernest and unadorned, a truthful and lovely track.

tracks.title: Dark Sea Dive
tracks.desc: Slow and atmospheric melodies played by warm synth pads, gives you a flowing motion of timelessness and fantasy.

tracks.title: Opportunity Knocks
tracks.desc: Blissful guitar and synth melodies are backed by quick, expressive drums and a happy bass line, loosening you up with a playful and happy-go-lucky song.

tracks.title: Planned Community
tracks.desc: A deep, prominent, yet pleasant bass line accents subtle drums. Organic, warm synth pads and glowing piano bring this fast paced song a sparkling childlike glee.

tracks.title: Out Of Necessity
tracks.desc: A close mic gives the warm piano chords of this upbeat track a resounding depth, the thoughtful melody has a open, accepting glow that rings with the dense chording.

tracks.title: Fare Thee Well
tracks.desc: A nocturnal sounding organ with dramatic chord changes in a constant slow moving rhythm keeps you in suspense.

tracks.title: Down The Aisle
tracks.desc: Cinematic and dancing melodies of the bright organ gives you the sense of a sudden dawn in a dark and medieval time.

tracks.title: Hymn Of Temptation
tracks.desc: Playful organ frolics around the keyboard, running through different themes and emotions. Warm and airy, the slightly merry tune is different from how you might expect organ music to sound.

tracks.title: Kyrie Eleison
tracks.desc: The combination of the calm organ and the more drastic, powerful organ together weave a dynamic track, throbbing with prayerful concentration and seriousness.

tracks.title: Morning Mass
tracks.desc: A energetic organ in a constant flowing tempo weaves a bright and powerful call to arise and shine, tooting and organic, the thrumming organ shakes the skies.

tracks.title: O Gloria
tracks.desc: A climactic organ weaves a melodramatic tune, exalting and joyfully bubbling with the fire of life.

tracks.title: Penitence Canon
tracks.desc: A joyous organ weaves an uplifting melody, echoing with spiritual energy, full of life's drama-  smiles, tears, and memorable moments.

tracks.title: Funeral March
tracks.desc: Appropriately reverent and mournful, long streams of organ chords open the mortal landscape for public memorial and private recompense.

tracks.title: MC Haydn Mass 12 in B Flat Major 2
tracks.desc: The organ and string section create a very regal feel to this setting of the Gloria. The arpeggiated strings during the forte sections create a very energetic feel to the movement. Vocal solos in a slower, more mournful setting are also featured.
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: MC Haydn Mass 12 in B Flat Major 3
tracks.desc: This setting of the Credo has stark contrasts between bright and majestic choral features and slow, mournful solos.  The solos become more closely integrated with the entirety of the choir, almost like a vocal concerto.
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: MC Haydn Mass 12 in B Flat Major 4
tracks.desc: This brief setting of Sanctus is very powerful, and brings an immediate feel of intensity when the solos finally climax into a fortissimo choral section.
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: MC Haydn Mass 12 in B Flat Major 5
tracks.desc: This setting of Benedictus continues in similar manner to the four previous movements, including bright, powerful strings and choral sections in stark contrast with solo sections.
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: MC Haydn Mass 12 in B Flat Major 6
tracks.desc: The Agnus Dei begins in a mysterious, powerfully sacred tone, then rests. Then the choir heralds steadfast, unwavering praise for a truly rousing finish.
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: MC Vivaldi Dixit Dominus di Praga RV 595 One
tracks.desc: A prim and proper baroque orchestra begins this first movement in a lively manner.  The orchestra is then joined by a cheerful four-part choir.
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: MC Vivaldi Dixit Dominus di Praga RV 595 Two
tracks.desc: The mournful second movement features a four-part choir singing in overlapping, contrapuntal style, accompanied by very simple yet solemn orchestrations
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: MC Vivaldi Dixit Dominus di Praga RV 595 Three
tracks.desc: An orchestra and harpsichord open this playful movement.  An alto solo follows the opening and continues for the remainder of the movement.
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: MC Vivaldi Dixit Dominus di Praga RV 595 Four
tracks.desc: Low-pitched strings and a duet between a soprano and alto are the highlight of this moderately fast movement.
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: MC Vivaldi Dixit Dominus di Praga RV 595 Five
tracks.desc: The full choir returns in this funeral-like movement.  A very slow tempo is taken, signifying a painful loss.  The jubilance only returns very briefly at the end of the movement.
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: MC Vivaldi Dixit Dominus di Praga RV 595 Six
tracks.desc: A florid and colorful mezzo-soprano solo is the central feature of this movement.  The soloist sings with much ornamentation in true Baroque style.
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: MC Vivaldi Dixit Dominus di Praga RV 595 Seven
tracks.desc: A trumpet solo backed by a quiet orchestra leads into a contemplative alto solo.  When the choir enters at the end, the pace picks up significantly, giving the movement an exuberant ending.
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: MC Vivaldi Dixit Dominus di Praga RV 595 Eight
tracks.desc: An emotional alto solo is backed by sparse strings in this melancholic movement.
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: MC Vivaldi Dixit Dominus di Praga RV 595 Nine
tracks.desc: An organ is heard at the beginning of this movement, which is joined by quiet orchestration and a baritone and tenor duet.  An alto soloist eventually joins in a contrapuntal syle.
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: MC Vivaldi Dixit Dominus di Praga RV 595 Ten
tracks.desc: This very brief movement hearkens to the first movement, with similar orchestration and choral arrangement.
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: MC Vivaldi Dixit Dominus di Praga RV 595 Eleven
tracks.desc: The work chooses to not end in a fast, lively manner, but rather in a more majestic setting, featuring a contrapuntal choir and steady strings.
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: MC Vivaldi Salve Regina RV 618 One
tracks.desc: Contrapuntal strings begin this movement, which are then joined by a harpsichord and graceful alto solo.
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: MC Vivaldi Salve Regina RV 618 Two
tracks.desc: An ornamented alto solo, strings, and organ make up this intense second movement.  Forceful, loud instrumentation is featured.
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: MC Vivaldi Salve Regina RV 618 Three
tracks.desc: This quiet and brooding movement once again features strings and an alto soloist, singing at a slower, more contemplative tempo.
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: MC Vivaldi Salve Regina RV 618 Four
tracks.desc: Woodwinds are more prominent in this movement than the others, with the previous staples of strings and an alto soloist still being used.
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: MC Vivaldi Salve Regina RV 618 Five
tracks.desc: The pace slows for the somber fifth movement, which brings the harpsichord into prominence.
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: MC Vivaldi Salve Regina RV 618 Six
tracks.desc: The work ends in a slow, solemn manner, with the alto soloist singing at a quiet volume over sparse orchestration.
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: MC Tchaikovsky Concerto for Piano and Orchestra 1 in B Flat Minor Opus 23 First Movement
tracks.desc: Regal horns, flowing strings, and resounding, virtuosic piano outline this famous first movement.  The piano part uses call-and-response techniques with pizzicato strings, as well as perfectly accenting the orchestra as a whole.
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: MC Tchaikovsky Concerto for Piano and Orchestra 1 in B Flat Minor Opus 23 Second Movement
tracks.desc: This slower movement mostly features interplay between strings and piano, with the piano remaining dominant throughout.
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: MC Tchaikovsky Concerto for Piano and Orchestra 1 in B Flat Minor Opus 23 Third Movement
tracks.desc: This boisterous final movement features Russian-like piano and orchestral sections that flow into slower, more legato sections in an exciting finale to this work.
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: MC Weber Piano Concerto 1 In C First Movement
tracks.desc: The first movement begins with a very regal feel coming from the strings, which is followed by a virtuosic piano solo with booming octaves and tight trills.  The movement ends with bombastic orchestrations.
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: MC Weber Piano Concerto 1 In C Second Movement
tracks.desc: Octaves and arpeggios classify the piano solo in this second movement, full of free-form arpeggiations and beautiful melody lines.  All of this is accented beautifully by the dreamy orchestra.
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: MC Weber Piano Concerto 1 In C Third Movement
tracks.desc: The remarkable piano playing of the soloist really comes to fruition in this final movement, which contains glorious piano lines accented by a clever orchestra who knows exactly how to let the piano shine.
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: MC Dvorak Te Deum Opus 103 1
tracks.desc: A thunderous orchestra and choir give great power to this first movement.  Solos from baritone and soprano are featured, interwoven with resounding percussion, strings, woodwinds, and brass.
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: MC Dvorak Te Deum Opus 103 2
tracks.desc: This movement is more reserved than the previous one, and features a calming baritone solo, backed by woodwinds, strings, and a four-part choir.
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: MC Dvorak Te Deum Opus 103 3
tracks.desc: A soaring soprano solo, as well as call-and-response between the females and males of the choir are some of the highlights of this both calming and exciting movement.  Lively brass and percussion give this movement a bombastic ending.
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: Close Up
tracks.desc: Smooth electronica track with a peaceful flow, pattering drums and bass synths pulse under a warm and absorbing atmosphere.
tracks.comp: Dean Barrett, APRA (50%), Judy Whittaker, APRA (50%)

tracks.title: MC Bizet L Arlesienne Suite 1 Opus 23 4 Carillon
tracks.desc: An exciting beginning and ending leave room for a slow, whimsical middle section.  Strings and winds set the tone, which borders on melancholy but also maintains an air of cheer.
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: MC Schubert Mass 2 in G Major D 167 One
tracks.desc: An amazing soprano solo is the highlight of this Kyrie, which features string orchestra and choir as well.
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: MC Schubert Mass 2 in G Major D 167 Two
tracks.desc: A male and female solo make up the central parts of this movement, surrounded by a thunderous response by the choir and orchestra.
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: MC Schubert Mass 2 in G Major D 167 Three
tracks.desc: The Credo begins and ends softly, but has a powerful middle.  The volume gradually increases up to the middle and decreases thereafter.
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: MC Schubert Mass 2 in G Major D 167 Four
tracks.desc: The piece begins with all parts of the choir singing together, and then goes into a contrapuntal section with all four sections of the choir singing separate melodies simultaneously.
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: MC Schubert Mass 2 in G Major D 167 Six
tracks.desc: The mass comes to a tranquil ending with the Agnus Dei, featuring a male and female solo separated by a choral section.
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: MC Schubert Mass 3 in B Flat Major (Kyrie)
tracks.desc: A bright orchestra sets a happy tone in this Kyrie. Male and female vocal solos are featured, as well as a full choir.
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: MC Schubert Mass 3 in B Flat Major (Gloria)
tracks.desc: An exciting opening from the choir and orchestra leads into a more subdued middle section, featuring a baritone and soprano solo. The initial jubilance returns at the end of the movement.
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: Good Ole Boy
tracks.desc: With salt of the earth ingenuity, this Bluegrass-tinged ditty sails by like a mid-summer evening breeze.
tracks.comp: Hal Goldstein, SESAC (50%), William Harlan Derby, BMI (50%)
tracks.pub: Music Of Freeplay, SESAC (50%), Freeplaymusic, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: Harvest Moon
tracks.desc: Light, airy and folky, this country lullaby will inspire dreams of far off places, thanks to the lucid accordion.

tracks.title: By The Bootstraps
tracks.desc: A propulsive rhythm rolls, accented by a dark, resonating bass line, a shimmering phased guitar plays ringing chords that add a dark, moody flow. Sliding guitar notes give a doppler effect to the phased chords.

tracks.title: Fast Learner
tracks.desc: A fat snare and thumping bass weave a jammy but pointed rhythm, dirty electric guitar brings hot riffing and a dark attitude. The flash and burn of this mid tempo track would lend it's self well to so-mo and contact sports.

tracks.title: Going Pro
tracks.desc: An propulsive rhythm pushes a nice, prog bass line with an upbeat, motivational groove. Electric guitar brings a sweet, syncopated melody that bounces off the bass riff, a second guitar weaves chords into a sunny atmosphere.

tracks.title: Half Time Rotation
tracks.desc: A eager bassline and a popping snare weave a progressive rhythm for lovely, reberbed guitar riffing. The mod guitar has a rockabilly feel that sounds totally modern.

tracks.title: In The Rink
tracks.desc: A blusey guitar leads this mid tempo rocker with a punchy, dirty grind. Big, slamming drums bring a dynamic rhythm as a round, fat bass pins down the beat.

tracks.title: Love Of The Game
tracks.desc: A bit of a country vibe flows through the rocking lead guitar on this driving track, a swinging tom fueled beat and a stepping bass nail the driving beat.

tracks.title: Offensive Strategy
tracks.desc: A groovy effected guitar weaves a gritty but upbeat melody as an assured 4 on the floor beat keeps pushing forward, a warm ringing bass adds a pulsing bottom as the band hits a jamming peak. Resourceful and motivational.

tracks.title: Preening Rookie
tracks.desc: A hot guitar weaves a boisterious melody with grinding chords as a slamming snare keeps an in the pocket beat, a jamming bass steps to the big rhythm with pulsing lines.

tracks.title: One Horse Town
tracks.desc: A slow, steady Bluegrass waltz with Cajun undertones, with delicately articulated banjo and a silky quilt of accordion.
tracks.comp: Hal Goldstein, SESAC (50%), William Harlan Derby, BMI (50%)
tracks.pub: Music Of Freeplay, SESAC (50%), Freeplaymusic, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: Open Your Eyes
tracks.desc: Synth beat pushes with dark force as a fuzzy bass lays a funky line. Handclaps and shakers keep the beat popping as organ weaves a repetitive melody. A soulful female voice sings a moody, emotional vocal.
tracks.pub: Kinkystyles Publishing, ASCAP (25%), Mike Genato Music, ASCAP (25%), Freeplaynjj, ASCAP (50%)

tracks.title: Evil Twins
tracks.desc: A steady, percussive and menacing rhythm create a sense of urgency, while a piano bass line suggest ulterior motives.

tracks.title: From The Inside
tracks.desc: Evolving melody from synth bleeps and organ chords kicks into a serious jam when the beat hits, twirling synths weave engaging melodies and  arpeggios swerve as the driving beat rolls underneath.
tracks.comp: Dean Barrett, APRA (50%), Judy Whittaker, APRA (50%)

tracks.title: Sounds Of The Island
tracks.desc: A laid back track with a sunny, humid feel- warm, blusey acoustic guitar solos float above a reggae-ish rhythm.

tracks.title: Summer Days
tracks.desc: Acoustic guitar weaves a rhythmic and upbeat melody, a second guitar brings bright and blusey solos playing sweetly with the rhythm guitar line.

tracks.title: MC Dvorak String Quartet 12 In F First Movement
tracks.desc: Strings play brilliant melody lines throughout this mostly fast-paced movement.
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: MC Dvorak String Quartet 12 In F Second Movement
tracks.desc: This much slower, somber movement features steady plucking from the low strings and elongated melody lines from the higher strings.
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: MC Dvorak String Quartet 12 In F Third Movement
tracks.desc: This movement is a combination of sorts of the previous two movements, with fast and vivacious passages interspersed with more slow and drawn out sections.
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: MC Dvorak String Quartet 12 In F Fourth Movement
tracks.desc: The violin plays a fast, lilting melody in this sprightly final movement.  The middle section of the movement has a brief slowdown, but the initial pace returns in the last section.
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: MC Dvorak String Quartet 13 In G First Movement
tracks.desc: The downbeat is often slightly difficult to find in this somewhat freeform movement, which includes many different tempos, time signatures, and dynamic levels.
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: MC Dvorak String Quartet 13 In G Second Movement
tracks.desc: This slow movement has a somewhat heavy feel, exemplified by the loud playing from the lower strings.
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: MC Dvorak String Quartet 13 In G Third Movement
tracks.desc: This movement has three distinct sections: a rapid beginning and ending, and a slower, more withdrawn middle.
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: MC Dvorak String Quartet 13 In G Fourth Movement
tracks.desc: This final movement doesn't stay at a fixed tempo for very long; energetic passages are frequently interspersed with slower sections.
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: MC Faure Quartet For Piano And Strings 1 In C Minor First Movement
tracks.desc: This first movement maintains a moderately fast and loud feel, with the piano and strings mostly playing at the same time.
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: MC Faure Quartet For Piano And Strings 1 In C Minor Second Movement
tracks.desc: Plucked strings provide a lilting backdrop for the piano in this fast, arpeggiated movement.
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: MC Faure Quartet For Piano And Strings 1 In C Minor Third Movement
tracks.desc: Sadness is evoked in this third movement, which features solemn, passionate playing from both strings and piano.
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: MC Faure Quartet For Piano And Strings 1 In C Minor Fourth Movement
tracks.desc: MC Faure Quartet For Piano And Strings 1 In C Minor Fourth Movement
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: MC Faure Quartet For Piano And Strings 2 In G Minor First Movement
tracks.desc: This sustained first movement ebbs and flows with excitement, as various crescendos and diminuendos give a rising and falling feel of intensity and suspense.
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: MC Faure Quartet For Piano And Strings 2 In G Minor Second Movement
tracks.desc: This pounding and scalar second movement features highly accented piano lines backed by mostly lower string sounds.
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: MC Faure Quartet For Piano And Strings 2 In G Minor Third Movement
tracks.desc: This slower movement features violin soli backed by music box-like piano lines.
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: MC Faure Quartet For Piano And Strings 2 In G Minor Fourth Movement
tracks.desc: The initial sustained feel of the first movement comes back in this final movement, which is a continuous array of sound from all the strings and piano.
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: MC Vivaldi Sinfonietta In B Minor First Movement
tracks.desc: Extended melodies pour from the flutes in this deeply sad movement.
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: MC Vivaldi Sinfonietta In B Minor Second Movement
tracks.desc: This walking-speed movement contains very measured melodies from lower and upper strings, and remains at a steady pace and volume.
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: MC Bach Suite 2 In B Minor First Movement
tracks.desc: Harpsichord and low, droning strings provide a backdrop for winds and high strings in this opening movement, full of contrapuntal melodies.
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: MC Bach Suite 2 In B Minor Second Movement
tracks.desc: Dance-like melodies from flute and violin fill this second movement.
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: MC Bach Suite 2 In B Minor Third Movement
tracks.desc: This movement is the slowest and most solemn of the movements in this work.  Mournful melodies pour from the flute and violins.
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: MC Bach Suite 2 In B Minor Fourth Movement
tracks.desc: This quick, lively movement is comprised of scalar violin and wind melodies.
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: MC Bach Suite 2 In B Minor Fifth Movement
tracks.desc: Sparse, staccato Baroque instrumentation makes up this detached, somewhat sad movement.
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: MC Bach Suite 2 In B Minor Sixth Movement
tracks.desc: Slow, waltz-like melodies are the central component of this brief, moderately-paced movement.
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: MC Bach Suite 2 In B Minor Seventh Movement
tracks.desc: This fiery final movement contains quickly moving melodic lines interchanged between the flute and violins.
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: MC Barsanti Sonata In B Flat First Movement
tracks.desc: Flute, cello, and harpsichord are the instruments used in this relaxed, somewhat free movement.
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: MC Barsanti Sonata In B Flat Second Movement
tracks.desc: A lovely melody from the flute is joined by the cello and harpsichord in this quickly paced movement.
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: MC Barsanti Sonata In B Flat Third Movement
tracks.desc: This slower movement once again contains interchange between harpsichord continuo, flute, and cello
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: MC Barsanti Sonata In B Flat Fourth Movement
tracks.desc: This brief final movement is bouncy and light, with late Medieval/early Baroque sounds prevailing throughout.
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: MC Beethoven Concerto for Piano and Orchestra No 2 in B Flat Major Opus 19 First Movement
tracks.desc: Rapidly moving scalar piano passages provide an impressive foreground to the orchestra in this exciting opening.
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: MC Beethoven Concerto for Piano and Orchestra No 2 in B Flat Major Opus 19 Second Movement
tracks.desc: Soothing sounds come from the piano in this relaxing movement.  The orchestra plays hushed chords in the background, giving a lullaby-like feel.
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: MC Beethoven Concerto for Piano and Orchestra No 2 in B Flat Major Opus 19 Third Movement
tracks.desc: This vivacious closer features standard resounding piano and orchestral chords building up to a bombastic finish.
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: MC Beethoven Quartet For Piano And Strings 2 In D First Movement
tracks.desc: A syncopated rhythm comes from the piano and strings in this lively opener.
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: MC Beethoven Quartet For Piano And Strings 2 In D Second Movement
tracks.desc: A sweet melody is executed by strings and piano in this moderately paced second movement.
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: MC Beethoven Quartet For Piano And Strings 2 In D Third Movement
tracks.desc: a fast triple meter is used in this final rondo movement.  Call-and-response techniques coupled with unison are employed in the instruments.
tracks.pub: Pleasantville Music Publishing, BMI (50%) and Freeplay Music, BMI (50%)

tracks.title: All The Way
tracks.desc: A laid-back r&b; sample rolls with a summery soul feel, an upbeat, streetwise rap speaks of meeting up with an old lover, and the changes that happen over time.

tracks.title: Look In The Mirror
tracks.desc: A string sample weaves a dramatic melody over a dirty street beat. The gritty, hard edged rap is an anti-gun rant that is very direct.

tracks.title: Making Headway
tracks.desc: This piece is built around intrigue, maintaining a calm and collected demeanor within the minimalist string and piano arrangements, even when the percussion kicks up the tempo.

tracks.title: Hope Is All Around
tracks.desc: A sanguine, introspective acoustic guitar theme, glistening like sunbeams on rain drops after a torrential storm.

tracks.title: Ride Across The Caucasus
tracks.desc: A stirring and melodic folk ballad, dramatically articulated on the acoustic guitar and driven by tribal hand percussion.
